        <h3>Privacy Statement</h3>
        <p class="h4 font-source">
           20overs.com ("20overs") provides various cricket game services including League Registration, Player Registration, Team Registration, scoring, Game Information and other services (collectively, the "Services"). 20overs is committed to safeguarding your privacy online and created this Privacy Statement in order to demonstrate our firm commitment to protecting the online privacy of users of our services.</p>
<p class="h4 font-source">By using the Services you consent to our gathering, use and disclosure of your information, as described in this Privacy Statement, the Terms of Service and the other documents, agreements and materials incorporated therein (collectively referred to as the "Rules"). This Privacy Statement may change from time to time and 20overs will provide notice of changes as described in the Terms of Service.</p>
<p class="h4 font-source">Questions regarding this Statement should be directed through the "Contact Us" section in this website (www.20overs.com/contactus).</p>


<h3>This Privacy Statement explains the following:</h3>
<ul class="list-group">
<li class="list-group-item h4">What information does 20overs gather?</li>
<li class="list-group-item h4">How does 20overs gather information?</li>
<li class="list-group-item h4">How does 20overs use the gathered information?</li>
<li class="list-group-item h4">With whom does 20overs share information we gather?</li>
<li class="list-group-item h4">How may you access or update stored information about you?</li>
<li class="list-group-item h4">How does 20overs protect your personal information?</li>
<li class="list-group-item h4">Use of Cookies; E-mail pixels.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1. What information does 20overs gather?</h3>
<p class="h4 font-source">20overs gathers information about you and your use of the Services as set forth below.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">Information about you. 20overs collects personal information about you including, without limitation, personally identifiable information (such as your name, address, phone number and e-mail address). For some of our Services we may also ask other information about you such as your age or other demographic information. 20overs may also collect your contact information and correspondence if you contact us by e-mail or letter.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">Information about your use of the Services. 20overs collects information about your use of the Services including, without limitation, data about your web browsing information (such as referring URL's as well as search words).</p>

<h3>2. How does 20overs gather information?</h3>
<p class="h4 font-source">20overs gathers information that you submit on any 20overs registration forms, questionnaires or other online forms. 20overs gathers information about your use of the Services during such use, and you understand that you are not anonymous to us. 20overs may also gather new information or update information from other sources including, for example, verifying and updating your address using third party services.</p>

<h3>3. How does 20overs use the gathered information?</h3>
<p class="h4 font-source">20overs uses your information to make your use of the Services more personalized and convenient. 20overs uses your information to display or deliver materials, such as e-mail notifications and content. 20overs may use your information to target such materials so that they may be more relevant to you than materials that would be provided without the use of your information. 20overs may provide your information to third parties as described below in Section 4.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">20overs uses your information to conduct and provide market research and data analysis services.<p class="h4 font-source">

<h3>4. With whom does 20overs share information we gather?</h3>

<p class="h4 font-source">20overs will not disclose your personally identifiable information to any third party, except if you have given us your consent for such disclosure or if the disclosure is described below. 20overs may share your non-personally identifiable information with third parties.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">20overs may share your personally identifiable information with third parties that provide services on behalf of 20overs. Such third parties do not have the right to use your information for any purpose other than to provide the applicable service.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">20overs may share your personally identifiable information with its affiliates that protect your personally identifiable information from disclosure to non-affiliated third parties in a manner similar to this Privacy Statement.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">If 20overs sells, assigns or transfers the part of its business that provides a particular Service to you, your personally identifiable information may be sold, assigned or transferred as a part of such transaction.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">20overs may disclose your personally identifiable information, any communications sent or received by you, and any other information that we may have about your account as follows: as may be required by law, regulation, rule or court order; pursuant to requests from governmental agencies or law enforcement authorities; as necessary to identify, contact or bring legal action against someone who may be violating the Rules; to operate the Services properly; or to protect 20overs, our members or other third parties including, without limitation, other emergency situations.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">Third Party Sites and Co-Branded Services. 20overs may advertise, promote, reference, recommend or provide links to third party sites, services and products. These third parties may have their own privacy policies, which may not comply with this Privacy Statement, even if the site, service or product is branded with 20overs' logo or name. 20overs IS NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR THE PRIVACY PRACTICES OF SUCH THIRD PARTIES OR ANY OTHER THIRD PARTIES. 20overs recommends that you review the privacy policies of any such third parties.</p>

<h3>5. How may you access or update stored Information about you?</h3>
<p class="h4 font-source">You may review and update your information stored as a part of your account in the Player profile area at any time. To access such information, please click on the "Talents" link after logging into your account. To update your profile, please click on the "Update My Profile" link.</p>

<h3>6. How does 20overs protect your personal information?</h3>
<p class="h4 font-source">All of your account information is password protected for your security. While 20overs believes that it has implemented reasonable security, 20overs cannot guarantee that our security measures will prevent unauthorized third parties, such as hackers, from obtaining or accessing your information.</p>

<h3>7. Use of Cookies; Email pixels</h3>
<p class="h4 font-source">20overs uses a feature of your Web browser called "cookies" to automate certain aspects of our Web site. Cookies are very small files that are stored on your computer and that enable us to recognize your computer each time you return to our site. By using cookies, 20overs can keep track of your preferences, what you have already seen on our site and what you haven't, and any personalization you've done, without requiring you to enter a password every time you come back. 20overs uses any information gathered using our cookies in compliance with this Privacy Statement.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">Third parties, including advertisers with whom 20overs may have a relationship, may also set cookies. Such third parties are responsible for placing and using such cookies and may collect information about you through such cookies; 20overs does not have access to such cookies, control the use of such cookies nor control over the privacy policy of such parties.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">We may use an e-mail delivery and marketing company to send you e-mails. Pixel tags and cookies are used in those e-mail messages and at our website to help us measure the effectiveness of our advertising and how visitors use our site.</p>

<p class="h4 font-source">The Privacy Statement posted on this site was updated in January, 2013.</p>

